    "created_at": "2012-10-19T19:58:00Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-10-19T19:58:00Z",
    "body": "That is not how I was thinking SharedOneShot would work. Maybe that's not the right name, since it isn't the same as SharedChan. I want a shared object that, the first time it is waited on performs the recieve, and subsequent times just looks at the value. Maybe a better composition would be some kind of `Mutex<Future<T>>` where `Future` can take a `OneShot` (Future currently only takes it's own pipe protocol).\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
