    "body": "Nominating for removal from milestone. [future_result](http://doc.rust-lang.org/std/task/struct.TaskBuilder.html#method.future_result) is sane enough now that it's not the end of the world to be stuck with it forever (it used to require capturing in- and moving back out of a closure).\n\nI still would rather this be a `spawn_result` method or something, so it doesn't break the builder pattern.\n",
